Functions:
	A function is reusable block of code.
	It can be called anywhere in the program.
Reusable code :  using an existing code without writing it every time we need.
	You can use the same code with different arguments to get different results.
JS:
Key word = function
( )
Parameters : values which are declared inside the ( ) while defining a functions.
Arguments :  values which are passed through the parameters

Ex:function with parameters
 function g(name){
        console.log("Hello "+name);
    }
    let name = prompt("Enter your name : ")
    g(name)
Return function : the return statement can be used to return the value to the function call
Ex:
function a(x,y){
return x+y;
}
let n1 = parseFloat(prompt(“Enter num1:”))
let n2 = parseFloat(prompt(“Enter num2:”))
//calling a function
let result = a(n1,n2)
console.log(“The sum is :”+result)
Anonymous function:
A function without name , after we create a function without name and we assign it to a variable
Ex:
sum = function(n1,n2){
let r = n1+n2
return r
}
console.log(sum(8,9))
